			<title>The Clock Is Ticking on Commercial Solar Incentives</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/news-events/the-clock-is-ticking-on-commercial-solar-incentives</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/news-events/the-clock-is-ticking-on-commercial-solar-incentives</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>Are you a commercial business – large or small – or a non-profit organization considering solar energy? Now is the time to act.</p>
<p>Recent legislation passed last summer eliminated and restricted key renewable energy tax incentives. While the 30% residential solar tax credit has ended for homeowners, the <strong>30% federal commercial solar tax credit is still available</strong> – but only for a limited time. This remaining incentive represents a significant opportunity for businesses and non-profits to reduce energy costs and invest in long-term sustainability.</p>
<h3>Why You Should Start Planning Now</h3>
<p><strong>Full 30% Tax Credit Through 2027</strong><br />Projects placed in service by <strong>December 31, 2027</strong>, are eligible for the full 30% federal tax credit. After that date, projects must meet the begin-construction exception as outlined below.</p>
<p><strong>Begin Construction by July 4, 2026<br /></strong><span style="caret-color: auto;">There is a path to still qualify for the tax credits for projects that begin construction on or before July 4, 2026. These projects can qualify under the exception to the 12/31/2027 placed-in-service cutoff, and (under current continuity safe harbor concepts) generally must be placed in service within four calendar years after the year construction begins—</span><strong style="caret-color: auto;">often end of 2029 (if begun in 2025) or end of 2030 (if begun in 2026)</strong><span style="caret-color: auto;">.</span></p>
<p>True to form, US tax code can be complicated and confusing, and there are important details that need to be understood to qualify. Please reach out to Lightwave to talk with our consultants about how you can get your commercial tax credits secured for your solar &amp; battery storage projects.</p>
<h3>Why Go Solar?</h3>
<ul>
<li>Lower long-term energy and operating costs</li>
<li>Invest in a clean, energy resilient future</li>
<li>Hedge against rate increases</li>
<li>Support environmental and ESG initiatives</li>
<li>Backup power to keep your business running</li>
</ul>
<h3>Why LightWave Solar?</h3>
<p>LightWave delivers customized, high-performance solar energy systems designed around your organization’s unique energy goals. Our turnkey approach covers every step, from design and installation to long-term service and support. Our solutions include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Battery backup systems</li>
<li>Roof-, ground-, and canopy-mounted solar arrays</li>
<li>Solar carports</li>
<li>EV charging stations</li>
</ul>
<p><img src="https://www.lightwavesolar.com/components/com_droppics/assets/images/t.gif" alt="" style="background: url('/components/com_droppics/assets/images/gallery.png') no-repeat scroll center center #D6D6D6; border: 2px dashed #888888; height: 200px; border-radius: 10px; width: 99%;" data-droppicsgallery="41" data-droppicsversion="3.3.1" data-gallery="41" /></p>
<h3>The Bottom Line</h3>
<p>The opportunity to secure the 30% commercial solar tax credit won’t last forever, and the timeline to qualify is already tightening. Starting the conversation now gives you the flexibility to plan, source materials strategically, and lock in savings before incentives disappear. The good news is that these incentives will still be around for battery back-up systems from now until 2032 for those who want to invest in back-up storage. Whatever your project, LightWave Solar is ready to help you move forward – confidently and on your timeline.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.lightwavesolar.com//book-a-consultation">Book your free consultation today!</a></p>]]></description>
